description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Lung Health Check specialist nurse to join the Respiratory department at UHCW, to support the Targeted Lung Health Check (TLHC) programme. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated band 6 Nurse with previous experience in treating patients with acute and chronic respiratory disease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a highly motivated, innovative, compassionate and enthusiastic registered nurse, who strives to deliver person-centred care, supported by excellent clinical knowledge and skills, is able to work autonomously and is confident in their own decision making. You ideally will have substantial experience working within the specialty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Targeted Lung Health Teams overall purpose is to enable the early detection of lung cancer in order to save lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is based at University Hospital Coventry &amp; Warwickshire and will have close alliances with general practitioners and the Community COPD team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jodie Storrow 02476237005&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJodie StorrowJob titleLead nurse - community COPD serviceEmail addressjodie.storrow@uhcw.nhs.ukTelephone number02476237005&lt;/p&gt;
